!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

regular /ˈrɛɡjʊlə/

(regulars) 

1. ADJ Regular events have equal amounts of time between them, so that they happen, for example, at the same time each day or each week. 定期的 

例： Get regular exercise. 定期进行锻炼。 

例： We're going to be meeting there on a regular basis. 我们将定期在那里见面。 

2. regularly ADV 定期地 [ADV with v] 

例： He also writes regularly for 'International Management' magazine. 他也定期为《国际管理》杂志写稿。 

3. ADJ Regular events happen often. 经常的 

例： Although it may look unpleasant, this condition is harmless and usually clears up with regular shampooing. 这可能不好看，但这种情况是无害的并且经常的洗头通常可以消除它。 

4. regularly ADV 经常地 [ADV with v] 

例： Fox, badger, and weasel are regularly seen here. 这里经常看得到狐狸、獾和黄鼠狼。 

5. ADJ If you are, for example, a regular customer at a shop or a regular visitor to a place, you go there often. 经常的 (顾客或来访者) [ADJ n] 

例： She has become a regular visitor to Houghton Hall. 她已成为霍顿府邸的一名常客。 

6. N-COUNT The regulars at a place or on a team are the people who often go to the place or are often on the team. 常客; 正式队员 

例： Regulars at his local bar have set up a fund to help out. 他的当地酒吧的常客们已经设立了一项基金来帮忙解决困难。 

7. ADJ You use regular when referring to the thing, person, time, or place that is usually used by someone. For example, someone's regular place is the place where they usually sit. 固定的 [det ADJ n] 

例： The man shook his hand and then sat at his regular table near the windows. 这个人握了握他的手，然后坐在他固定的靠窗的桌子旁。 

8. ADJ A regular rhythm consists of a series of sounds or movements with equal periods of time between them. 均匀的 

例： ...a very regular beat. …非常均匀的节拍。 

9. regularly ADV 均匀地 [ADV with v] 

例： Remember to breathe regularly. 记住要均匀地呼吸。 

10. ADJ Regular is used to mean 'normal.' 普通的 [美国英语] [ADJ n] 

例： The product looks and burns like a regular cigarette. 这种产品看上去和点起来都像一支普通的香烟。 

11. ADJ In some restaurants, a regular drink or quantity of food is of medium size. 中份的 [美国英语] [ADJ n] 

例： ...a cheeseburger and regular fries. …一个干酪汉堡包和中份的炸薯条。 

12. ADJ A regular pattern or arrangement consists of a series of things with equal spaces between them. 间隔一致的 

例： The village was laid out in regular patterns. 这个村庄街道和房屋被以相等的间隔整齐地加以布局。 

13. ADJ If something has a regular shape, both halves are the same and it has straight edges or a smooth outline. 规则的 

例： ...some regular geometrical shape. …一些规则的几何图形。 

14. regularity N-UNCOUNT 规则性 

例： ...the chessboard regularity of their fields. …国际象棋棋盘的规则性。 

15. ADJ In grammar, a regular verb, noun, or adjective inflects in the same way as most verbs, nouns, or adjectives in the language. (动词、名词或形容词) 按规则变化的

